{
  "texts": [
    "A comparison of dose calculation between sCT and CT is generally performed using specific regions of interest (ROI) for both photon (f) and proton (p) RT.",
    "The most commonly used voxel-based metric dose difference (DD) is calculated by taking the average dose (D CT D sCT) of the ROI and redistributing it across the whole body, target, or other structures of interest.",
    "DD is expressed as a percentage of the prescribed dose (%) or the maximum dose (Gy), either relative to it or an absolute value.",
    "TABLE 1 Metrics reported in literature for synthetic image analysis using ground truth as reference.",
    "Intensity Based Metrics Mean Error"
  ]
}